setTimeout(() => console.log("Timer 2"), 2000);
clearAllTimeouts();

Expected Output: No output

Explanation:
- Two setTimeouts are scheduled to log messages after 1 and 2 seconds respectively.
- `clearAllTimeouts()` is called before any of the timers complete.
- As a result, "Timer 1" and "Timer 2" are never logged because their timers were cleared.
Example 2:
Operations: 
const timer1 = setTimeout(() => console.log("This will print"), 500);
const timer2 = setTimeout(() => console.log("This will not print"), 1500);
setTimeout(() => {
    clearAllTimeouts();
}, 1000);

Expected Output: "This will print"
Explanation:
- The first timer is set to log after 500ms and does execute.
- The second timer would log after 1500ms but is cleared by `clearAllTimeouts()`.
- Only the output from the first timer is seen because it completes before the call to `clearAllTimeouts()`.

